The paper deals with algorithms for finding simple shortest paths and cycles in a weighted directed graph, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and algorithms. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem and presents new algorithms for generating simple cycles and paths. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses hardness results and graph theory, which makes cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible sub-categories, although less likely.
